==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[unit]] [[circle]]''' (''plural'' '''unit circles''')

#{{geometry}} A circle of [[radius]] 1.
#{{trigonometry}} ('''the unit circle''') The circle of radius 1 with centre at the [[origin]], used in defining [[trigonometric function]]s.

====Usage notes====
*'''Unit circle''' is seldom used in the simple geometric sense, where "a circle of radius 1" is much more common.

